Hello @thomas-mangin,

There seems to be a problem when trying to declare multiple groups with different BGP peers and processes definition: all processes are receiving all messages from all groups. 

Let's say you have the following ExaBGP configuration:

```
group group1 {
  process external1 {
    encoder json;
    peer-updates;
    neighbor-changes;
    receive-routes;
    run external.py;
  }
  neighbor 10.140.0.1 {
    router-id 192.168.37.128;
    local-address 192.168.37.128;
    local-as 65501;
    peer-as 65500;
    family {
      inet4 unicast;
      inet6 unicast;
    }
  }
}
group group2 {
  process external2 {
    encoder json;
    peer-updates;
    neighbor-changes;
    receive-routes;
    run external.py;
  }
  neighbor 10.140.0.2 {
    router-id 192.168.37.128;
    local-address 192.168.37.128;
    local-as 65501;
    peer-as 65500;
    family {
      inet4 unicast;
      inet6 unicast;
    }
  }
}
```

The external.py script is just dumping everything it receives in a file:

```
#!/usr/bin/env python

import sys, select, os

handle = open('/tmp/x%d.log' % os.getpid(), 'a+');
while True:
    ready, _, _ = select.select([sys.stdin], [], [], 1)
    if ready:
        line = sys.stdin.readline().strip()
        handle.write(line + "\n")
        handle.flush()
```

When starting the daemon (v3.4.10), I get this:

```
$ exabgp external.conf
\[...\]
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:32 | INFO     | 29945  | reactor       | New peer setup: neighbor 10.140.0.2 local-ip 192.168.37.128 local-as 65501 peer-as 65500 router-id 192.168.37.128 family-allowed in-open
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:32 | INFO     | 29945  | reactor       | New peer setup: neighbor 10.140.0.1 local-ip 192.168.37.128 local-as 65501 peer-as 65500 router-id 192.168.37.128 family-allowed in-open
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:32 | WARNING  | 29945  | configuration | Loaded new configuration successfully
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:32 | INFO     | 29945  | processes     | Forked process external2
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:32 | INFO     | 29945  | processes     | Forked process external1
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:35 | INFO     | 29945  | network       | Connected to peer neighbor 10.140.0.1 local-ip 192.168.37.128 local-as 65501 peer-as 65500 router-id 192.168.37.128 family-allowed in-open (out)
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:35 | INFO     | 29945  | network       | Connected to peer neighbor 10.140.0.2 local-ip 192.168.37.128 local-as 65501 peer-as 65500 router-id 192.168.37.128 family-allowed in-open (out)
^CSun, 17 May 2015 19:49:53 | INFO     | 29945  | reactor       | ^C received
