Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:54 | INFO     | 29945  | processes     | Terminating process external2
Sun, 17 May 2015 19:49:54 | INFO     | 29945  | processes     | Terminating process external1
```

Both resulting files contain the exact same messages:

```
$ ls -al /tmp/x*.log
-rw-r----- 1 root root 4089 mai   17 19:49 /tmp/x29948.log
-rw-r----- 1 root root 4089 mai   17 19:49 /tmp/x29949.log

$ diff -s  /tmp/x*.log
Les fichiers /tmp/x29948.log et /tmp/x29949.log sont identiques
```

Is there a way to segregate messages for each group and send them only to the associated process? I saw a message referring to "group-updates not being enabled by default" in ExaBGP log but I couldn't find any documentation. The exact lines were:

```
group-updates not enabled for peer 10.140.0.1, it surely should, the default will change to true soon
group-updates not enabled for peer 10.140.0.2, it surely should, the default will change to true soon
``` 

(I'm not sure it's even relevant to that particular problem...)

Thanks,
Pierre-Yves

use https://github.com/mikeal/deferred to create a sans-io version of Client (SansIOClient) that requires something like:
```python
class SimpleStream(object):
    def next(self) -> Deferred:
        ...

class IOAdapter(object):
    def request(self, **kwargs) -> Deferred:
        ...

    def stream(self, **kwargs) -> SimpleStream:
        ...

    def unwrap_deferred(self, deferred: Deferred) -> Any:
        ...
```

and then implement it with something like:
```python
class BlockingSimpleStream(SimpleStream):
    def __init__(self, stream):
        self.generator = _stream_helper(stream):
    def next(self) -> Deferred:
        return deferred.succeeded(next(self.generator))

class BlockingIOAdapter(IOAdapter):
    def __init__(session: requests.Session):
        self.session = session

    def request(self, **kwargs) -> Deferred:
        return deferred.execute(self.session.request, **kwargs)

    def stream(self, **kwargs) -> BlockingSimpleStream:
        return BlockingSimpleStream(self.session.request(**kwargs, stream=True))

    def unwrap_deferred(self, d: Deferred):
        return deferred.waitForDeferred(d).getResult()
```

